            <section id="overview" class="legal-section">
                <h2><span class="section-number">1</span>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    CatchSpend ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application and related services (collectively, the "Service").
                </p>
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Privacy-First Design:</strong> CatchSpend is built with privacy at its core. Your expense data is stored locally on your device by default. We only collect what's necessary to provide our services.</p>
                </div>
                <p>
                    By using CatchSpend, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the application.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="data-collection" class="legal-section">
                <h2><span class="section-number">2</span>Data We Collect</h2>

                <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address, name, and password when you create an account</li>
                    <li><strong>Expense Data:</strong> Transaction amounts, merchant names, categories, dates, and notes you enter</li>
                    <li><strong>Receipt Images:</strong> Photos of receipts you scan using our camera feature</li>
                    <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> Your app settings, currency preferences, and category customizations</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system version, unique device identifiers</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Features used, time spent in app, crash reports</li>
                    <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited (for web services)</li>
                </ul>

